HEADWORD: Inermis
<hw>In*er"mis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inermis</ets>, <ets>inermus</ets>; pref. <ets>in-</ets> not +
<ets>arma</ets> arms: cf. F. <ets>inerme</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Unarmed; destitute of prickles or thorns, as a leaf.</def>
